content: MOSCOW, May 3 (Reuters) - The Kremlin said on Wednesday that Russia will continue talks with the United Nations and other parties to the Black Sea grain deal, and that Russia would not do anything to harm its own interests.

Earlier, Russian Foreign Ministry spokeswoman Maria Zakharova said talks between Russia and the United Nations on the Black Sea grain deal will be held in Moscow on May 5, with the U.N. represented by top trade official Rebeca Grynspan. (Reporting by Reuters)
